  <div id="sidebar"> 
   <div id="reporting_crime" class="rounded"> 
    <h3>Resources for serious situations</h3> 
    <p>UW-Madison has resources to assist victims and witnesses of crime, as well as other difficult situations:</p> 
    <ul> 
     <li><a href="http://oed.wisc.edu/childabuse/">Child abuse and neglect</a></li> 
     <li><a href="http://uhs.wisc.edu/assault/">Sexual assault, dating violence and stalking</a></li> 
     <li><a href="http://www.oed.wisc.edu/sexualharassment/">Sexual harassment</a></li> 
     <li><a href="http://www.students.wisc.edu/safety/">Concern for students by instructional staff and parents</a></li> 
     <li><a href="http://www.students.wisc.edu/safety/campus-threat-assessment-policies/">Threat assessment policies</a></li> 
    </ul> 
    <p>In all cases, you can also always contact the <a href="http://uwpd.wisc.edu/">UW Police Department</a> for assistance.</p> 
